cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper proposes a framework for image-to-image transformations using convolutional neural networks and adversarial training. The focus is on computer vision tasks, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of adversarial training and neural networks also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions semantic labels and scene images, which could indicate a connection to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
